<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="68" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1322,724,910]" box="[264,366,724,749]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis box="[264,366,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1322,724,910]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">
The specimens were reared from the pupae of 
<taxonomicName box="[851,1079,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chamaesphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schizoceriformis">
<emphasis box="[851,1079,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">C. schizoceriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which bores into the roots of 
<taxonomicName box="[365,644,804,829]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boissieriana">
<emphasis box="[365,644,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Euphorbia boissieriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and pupates there. This record is of particular interest in that species of 
<taxonomicName box="[453,640,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chamaesphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[453,640,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Chamaesphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Europe have been released in North 
<collectingCountry box="[1176,1277,844,870]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">America</collectingCountry>
for control of introduced weedy members of the 
<taxonomicName box="[792,887,884,909]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="esula">
<emphasis box="[792,887,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">E. esula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex (
<bibRefCitation author="Julien" box="[1010,1298,884,910]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" refString="Julien, M. H. &amp; Griffiths, M. W. (1998) Biological control of weeds: a world catalogue of agents and their target weeds. CABI Publishing, Wallingford. x + 223 pp." type="book" year="1998">
Julien &amp; Griffiths, 
<number box="[1235,1298,884,910]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
